      children: "The Memorial Stupa, Thimphu, also known as the Thimphu Chorten, is located in the southern-central part of the city near the main roundabout and Indian military hospital. The chorten, built in 1974 to honor the third Druk Gyalpo, Jigme Dorji Wangchuck (1928\u20131972), is a prominent landmark in the city with its golden spires and bells. The Memorial Chorten of Thimphu was conceived by Thinley Norbu Rinpoche (1931\u20132011),according to the Nyingma tradition of Tibetan Buddhism. The main patron was the Druk Gyalpo\u2019s mother, Phuntsho Choden. In 2008, it underwent extensive renovation. It was consecrated by Dudjom Jigdral Yeshe Dorje."
