      children: "Nalanda Buddhist Institute, also known locally as Daley Goenpa or Dalida, is a Buddhist monastic school. The shedra is located in the western part of the Punakha District in the Kingdom of Bhutan. It is located below Talo Monastery and is above Walakha. It is about a 25-minute drive from the main highway to Punakha, before reaching Kuruthang from the Metsina junction. Nalanda Buddhist Institute can be seen from Dochu La pass and from Thinleygang on the main East-West highway."
